attered antique, a blind man carrying a lantern, sutras set on fire, a cow jumping through a window—each story leads the reader to reflect on fundamental Buddhist ideas.The Ways of Zen also features the original Chinese text in side columns on each page, enriching the book for readers and students of Chinese without distracting from the English-language cartoons.Filled with memorable anecdotes and disarming wisdom, The Ways of Zen is a perfect introduction to Zen Buddhism and an essential addition to any Zen collection.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aZen BuddhismvComic books, strips, etc. 7aRELIGION / Buddhism / Zen (see also PHILOSOPHY / Zen).2bisacsh  aChinese philosophy.  aTsai Chih Chung.  abeliefs.  abestselling comics.  abilingual edition.  abooks by Tsai.  aclassical Chinese.  acomics.  aeastern philosophy.  afamous Asian cartoonists.  agifts for Chinese readers of English.  agifts for students of Chinese.  aideas.  aillustrated Chinese philosophy.  anonfiction comics.  aphilosophical comics.  aphilosophy comics.  areligion.  atenets.  aunderstanding Zen Buddhism.1 aBatchelor, Martine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBruya, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBruya, Brian.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2021 Englishz978311075419308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2021z9783110753974oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Pr